When cutting firewood saw a very unusual hornet/wasp very large. After hearing an story about Asian Hornets on the radio I looked at web and that was the insect that I tried to kill.

We were camping in kittitas county when it landed on my friend. She freaked out and it flew away. It was approximately 1 and half inch long, stripped body with mostly black and yellowish/orangeish head.

(3) Sightings, absolutely no question Asian hornet, they are so big and thick, not like any other wasp or hornet. I live on Highland Dr in Port Ludlow, due to the virus I have been home more and doing some paintin in my garage. (3) times I have seen this
Seen on a security camera, so I can't be certain of size but it looks big

I did not get a picture it flew into the garage then flew out.  Was about the size of an adult male thumb long and wide.  It almost looked brown with proprtional thinkness of black and yellow stripes appeared to have a stinger.
I killed one not sure what is was about 2.5 cm long. I have a picture on my computer, but don't know how to add to this form
